CatDescriptText: Marilyn Stewart, housewife, 427 Fairywood Street, was part of the "Pittsburghers Speak Up" column published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 21, 1959, pg. A1 with question: "Do you think that the steel strike will be resumed after the 80-day 'cooling-off' period imposed by the Supreme Court under the injection of the Taft-Hartley Act?" answer reads: "They probably will and I feel as though there will not be a settlement."
TitMainTitle: Portrait of Marilyn Stewart wearing light colored coat with floral lining, standing in front of bus or trolley with man standing on right
